<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,261,396]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,261,288]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from all other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Townes in Townes &amp; Townes" authorityYear="1960" box="[930,1058,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Acrotaphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[930,1058,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Acrotaphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of the following characters: 1) margin of gena behind eyes flat in dorsal view; 2) posterior ocelli separated from eyes by 0.2× its diameter in dorsal view; 3) metasoma orange with tergites V+ black; 4) tarsal claw with basal lobe longitudinally elongated, with claw apex clearly overtaking the posterior margin of lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
